The SSID setting fresh from the factory is unknown. ==Additional external links== ===Forums=== *[https://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?pid=92872 ''Success with Belkin F5D9230-4!'' - '''OpenWrt''' Forums] *[https://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?id=32667 ''Belkin F5D9230-4 v3000'' - '''OpenWrt''' Forums] *[https://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?id=17124 ''Belkin G + Mimo router - is it supported? has anybody tried it?'' - '''OpenWrt''' Forums] *[http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=57834 ''Belkin F5D9230-4 v3000uk support?'' - '''DD-WRT''' Forums] *[http://www.dd-wrt.com/phpBB2/viewtopic.php?t=27890 ''Belkin F5D9230-4 V3100 RDC x86'' - '''DD-WRT''' Forums] ===Other=== *[http://warrantyvoidifremoved.blogspot.com/2010/08/unbricking-belkin-wireless-router.html ''Unbricking a Belkin Wireless Router'' @ '''warrantyvoidifremoved.blogspot.com'''] ==Images== File:Belkin F5D9230-4 v3 angled.jpg|angled File:Belkin F5D9230-4 v3 bottom.jpg|bottom File:Belkin F5D9230-4 v3 back.jpg|back File:Belkin F5D9230-4 v3 power adapter.jpg|power adapter [[Has images::external| ]][[Has images::label| ]][[Has images::power adapter| ]] File:Belkin F5D9230-4 v3 board top.jpg|board top File:Belkin F5D9230-4 v3 board bot.jpg|board bottom [[Has images::internal| ]] ==Included PSU(s)== The power adapter included with the device in the US is a '''Rong-Horng Electronic''' RH41-1200500DU. {{hasPowerSupply |brand=Rong-Horng Electronic |model=RH41-1200500DU |input_v=120 |input_a=0.133 |input_c=AC |input_hz=60 |input_conn=NEMA 1-15P |output_v=12 |output_a=0.5 |output_c=DC |output_conn=barrel |style=large, vertical }}
